LIC LIBRARIES IN LOCAL COOPERATIVE SYSTEMS.     DEALS WITH NETWORKING AND ITS IMPLICATIONS FOR MEMBER LIBRARIES OF ACOOPERATIVE SYSTEM IN NEW YORK STATE. AFTER DESCRIBING BRIEFLY LIBRARYDEVELOPMENTS IN THE STATE, DISCUSSES THE HISTORY, ORGANISATION, AND FINANCINGOF THE NASSAU LIBRARY SYSTEM. THE SERVICE PROGRAMME OF THE SYSTEM IS OUTLINED,AND THESE ACTIVITIES ARE THEN RELATED TO STATEWIDE, REGIONAL, BICOUNTY, ANDLOCAL ACTIVITIES WHICH HAVE AN IMPACT ON LOCAL LIBRARY SERVICE. THE PROBLEMSOF NEW YORK SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT ARE MENTIONED, AND THE BENEFITS OFPARTICIPATION IN A SYSTEM PROGRAMME ARE DISCUSSED